  "comment": "Per-scenario regression config for tests/Aws2Azure.PerfTests. Two gates: (1) ABSOLUTE floors/ceilings in 'scenarios' (minThroughputPerSec / maxP99Ms), enforced per-test by PerfResult.AssertNoRegression — either field 0 opts out of that half; kept only as wide catastrophe-detectors on emulator-bound paths that have no azure-sdk.* baseline to pair against. (2) RELATIVE proxy-vs-baseline ratios in 'pairings', enforced once per run by RelativeRegressionGateTests (Category=RelativeGate) reading docs/perf/baseline-latest.json. The relative gate is the meaningful signal: emulator tail-latency jitter hits BOTH the proxy and its azure-sdk.* baseline, so the ratio cancels the noise and fails only when the PROXY adds overhead. METRIC BY SHAPE: REST + AMQP-receive pairs gate on p99-ratio (unimodal, stable); AMQP-SEND pairs gate on p50-ratio ONLY (bimodal cold-link-attach tail makes p99-ratio swing 0.06x-11x run-to-run — the median is the stable steady-state-overhead signal). A 0 ratio opts out of that dimension. azure-sdk.* baselines are reference rulers — {0,0} absolute, never fail the build. Operators bump these deliberately when a proxy change is expected to move performance. EVERY scenario must have a 'scenarios' entry — KnownPerfScenariosTests asserts coverage.",
